entries.meaning: (nautical) The flow of air so deflected

verbs.description: backwind (third-person singular simple present backwinds, present participle backwinding, simple past and past participle backwinded)

entries.meaning: (nautical) To deflect air into the back of a sail or of a vessel
examples: If a sailing boat's bow is pointing too high into the wind the sails backwind.

verbs.description: backwind (third-person singular simple present backwinds, present participle backwinding, simple past and past participle backwound)

examples: This works because tape packs with equal diameters also have equal circumferences, therefore the distance the tape on each deck travels when backwound from the edit point is the same.
